    /*
    The discrete convolution of two signals A and B is defined as:

          A.length
    C[i] = Σ (A[k]*B[i-k])
          k=0

    It's obvious that:  0 <= k <= A.length , 0 <= i <= A.length + B.length - 2  and  0 <= i-k <=
